[thinking] **Considering error handling in class loading**
[thinking] 
[thinking] The user mentioned catching errors but only if it's related to fundamentally open-ended dynamic class loading. I’m thinking we could handle UnsupportedFeatureError when instantiating? But the tests are expected to run, making this a bit tricky. Native Image might restrict ClassLoader, and I wonder if ClassLoader.loadClass on existing classes might throw errors. Class.forName with a constant string seems supported if metadata is handled properly, but custom loadClass could lead to no dynamic behavior.
